\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 One possible solution involves the use of flex sensors to recognize various unique hand gestures based on finger bending. These hand gestures could be tested and developed to map out specific phrases or the entire American Sign Language alphabet. This use 
of flex sensors to identify hand gestures is vastly different from the other possible implementations which rely on the position of the entire hand to gather input data. Instead of tracking the hand as one moving block, this design solution tracks each ind
ividual finger to provide a larger range of possible inputs. Operation of the glove would require no arm movement and users could customize their own gestures to perform common computing tasks. This design is superior in that it can recognize a greater num
ber of inputs (gestures) but has the drawback of complex implementation. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
