\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Because this implementation only changes the way data is gathered and interpreted, and not the appearance of the final product, this customer requirement would remain unchanged}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Easy to set up/use}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 By lacking an IMU or camera system, the flex sensor implementation is quick to start up and requires no calibration time. The intended nature of the glove as a finger position mapper could allow incredible responsiveness once a user becomes accustomed to i
t. This responsiveness is due to the natural use of fingers as communication mediums in our daily lives. However without the required accuracy specified above, none of these features would be possible. Product research regarding flex sensors has pointed ou
t reliability issues regarding the connection lead stability. When bent to extremes (like the curve of a bent finger) the flex sensors tend to break or deliver incorrect readings.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Portable}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The portability of this implementation is superior to that of the web cam based model because it doesn\'81\'66t require a stationary web cam, and all necessary data measurement hardware is incorporated into the glove. This allows for a greater level of environmen
tal flexibility when using the product. The inclusion of a battery system and wireless communication allows for remote communication to the computer.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Inexpensive}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The cost of the device would include the wireless hardware, 4 to 5 flex sensors, 4 to 8 touch sensors, and a microcontroller. After adding the estimated costs for each element, the final price to build a prototype comes to $180, leaving little room to make
 a profit while meeting this customer requirement.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Safe to Use}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 By using flex sensors, the microcontroller would not have to carry out double integration and instead would read simple voltages and convert them to digital values. By avoiding complex arithmetic only small amounts of heat will be generated by the microcon
troller.  The conclusion drawn is that heat would not be an issue.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Compact}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Little would change in the overall dimensions of the product when compared to the alternative design solutions. By removing the IMU a small amount of circuit board real estate is salvaged. In that regard, the device hardware is smaller than that of the alt
ernatives. The flex sensor implementation also houses all measurement hardware on the glove itself, leading to a compact design.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Intuitive}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 If constructed and calibrated properly, this device would be able to recognize a wide range of user generated inputs to control many possible computer functions. By lacking an IMU, this implementation cannot detect hand movements or sudden jolts to the sys
tem such as taps.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Complexity of Design(benefits/costs)}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1081\ltrch\dbch\af3\langfe2052\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Each flex sensor acts as a variable resistor, which could be configured to output a range of voltages. This voltage would then be measured by an ADC to then be output to the microcontroller. The problem lies in the fact that the voltages must be converted 
to discrete values to be  useful. This is difficult to accomplish due to the variability of each flex resistor. Over time each flex resistor would wear out and need unique calibration to be accurate. The overall cost of the system is impacted by the price 
of flex sensors, powering the  not low enough to meet our price point of $200. The benefits of using this implementation is that it could potentially have many unique inputs coming from 4-5 sensors. The major drawback is the unreliable nature of flex resis
tors as the main data gathering sensor.}
